First Read: 03-Mar-26
HB536 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 Relating to Henry County; to further provide for the
4 compensation of the sheriff; and to repeal Section 45-34-230,
5 Code of Alabama 1975, relating to the compensation of the
6 sheriff.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
8 Section 1. (a) Beginning June 1, 2026, the Sheriff of
9 Henry County shall receive an additional expense allowance in
10 an amount that brings his or her total compensation to
11 ninety-four thousand dollars ($94,000) per year.
12 (b) Beginning January 18, 2027, the base annual salary
13 for the sheriff shall be ninety-four thousand dollars
14 ($94,000) per year, in lieu of all other expense allowances or
15 other forms of compensation.
16 (c)(1) Notwithstanding subsection (b), beginning
17 January 18, 2027, any individual serving as sheriff shall
18 receive an increase in his or her then-existing salary of
19 eight percent for each second or subsequent successive term to
20 which he or she is elected sheriff.
21 (2) An individual who returns to the office of sheriff
22 for any non-successive term shall be compensated as if he or
23 she has obtained the office of sheriff for the first time, and
24 shall be eligible for increases pursuant to subdivision (1)
25 only for currently successive service.
26 (d) The sheriff shall receive all benefits provided to
27 employees of the Henry County Commission, but he or she shall
28 not be eligible for any increases in compensation pursuant to
Page 1

not be eligible for any increases in compensation pursuant to
HB536 Enrolled
29 Chapter 2A of Subtitle 1 of Title 11, Code of Alabama 1975.
30 Section 2. Section 45-34-230, Code of Alabama 1975,
31 relating to the compensation of the Sheriff of Henry County,
32 is repealed.
33 Section 3. This act shall become effective on June 1,
34 2026.
